  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Numbers now - and the number row is the longest reach on the whole keyboard, up top above the letters. Left hand first: 1 to 5. The move is reach up, hit it, snap back home. That snap-back is the whole skill."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Each digit uses the same finger as the letter below it. 1 is left pinky, 2 is left ring, 3 is left middle, 4 is left index, 5 is left index stretching one over. Reach with one finger only, keep the others on home, no peeking down."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "⬆️",
      "title": "Reach, don't relocate",
      "text": "Only the finger you need goes up. Don't lift the whole hand off home or you lose your anchor and end up hunting. Use the number row, not the numpad - that is a different skill for another day."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "1 2 3",
      "baseReps": 6,
      "keys": ["1", "2", "3"],
      "target": "1 2 3 1 2 3 1 2 3 1 2 3 1 2 3 1 2 3",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "Digits 1 2 3",
      "hint": "1 pinky, 2 ring, 3 middle. Reach up, tap, back to home, space after each."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "4 5",
      "baseReps": 10,
      "keys": ["4", "5"],
      "target": "4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5 4 5",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Digits 4 5",
      "hint": "Both left index: 4 straight up, 5 one step right. Stretch and return."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Fingers know where 1 to 5 live now. Let's chain them - single digits, then pairs, then longer runs. Keep it even, no rushing the stretch."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "Numbers type blind just like letters - from their own key, no looking down. It feels weird for a day, then it's automatic.",
      "by": "Jordan"
    },
